<TITLE> Premier cricket resumes Monday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 1 (bdnews24.com)  Following a three-day break after the Bangladesh Rifles mutiny in the capital, the Premier Cricket League resumes on Monday. Partex SC take on Young Pegasus at the Bangladesh Krira Shikkha Protisthan ground while BKSP face newcomers Cricket Coaching School at the Narayanganj Osmani Stadium as part of the revised schedule. All four teams occupy the bottom places of the 12-team table with unbeaten Bangladesh Biman atop with 12 points from six outings, two ahead of holders Abahani and Surjo Tarun. According to the revised schedule, two matches will be held per day instead of three as the Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium will be prepared for the upcoming Bangladesh home series against Pakistan, scheduled for March 7-22. The national cricket squad might be declared on March 4 or 5 and the next day the preparation will begin. The selected cricketers will also get permission to play their Premier League matches till the eighth round. bd
